# tests/integration/

Tests that exercise **multiple components together with real adapters** —
a real database, a real message queue, a real HTTP client against a
sandboxed peer. Slower than unit tests; faster than e2e.

Belongs here:
- Repository implementations against a real database (or testcontainers)
- Application services with their real infrastructure dependencies wired up
- Migrations applied to a real schema
- Adapter contracts (does our wrapper correctly translate the upstream API)

Does **not** belong here:
- Pure-logic tests that don't need a real backend — those go in `../unit/`
- Full user-flow scenarios across the deployed system — those go in `../e2e/`

Each test should set up and tear down its own state; tests must be
runnable in any order.

Canonical reference: `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/general/testing.md`.
